  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Full Time Assistant Adventure Guide",
  "description": "<p>LOCATION: RAINFOREST WILD ASIA (MANDAI)</p><p><br /></p><p>As an adventure guide, your main role is to ensure all patrons leave the site happy and have a \"tremendous\" time.</p><p>As such the quality of our services is just as important as the quality of our infrastructure.</p><p>We therefore expect guides to:</p><ul><li>Be happy and bring positive vibe into his/her working environment</li><li>Articulate with good interpersonal skills and pro-actively engage with customers in small talk</li><li>Confident in handling all customer profiles, even the most difficult</li><li>Fit and interested in outdoor activity to inspire customers' confidence</li></ul><p>The team of guides is also expected to follow the Forest Adventure Safety Management System (SMS) at all times which includes:</p><ul><li>Opening and closing safety checks of the course and its equipment</li><li>Maintain the course and ensure that is safe for operations</li><li>Conduct safety briefing</li><li>Standard Operating Procedure in managing customers on the course</li><li>Ensure patrons are comfortable while maneuvering through the obstacles</li><li>Will require to host and facilitate corporate group programmes</li></ul><p>Job Requirements</p><ul><li>Passionate about outdoors and work @ height</li><li>Able to work in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Basic First Aid is a plus</li><li>Great listener, communicator and team player</li><li>Physically Fit</li><li>No experience needed. Training will be provided</li><li>5 days' work week including weekends and PHs </li></ul>",
